      "Operators manually manipulated main burner isolation valve",
      "Facility shut-in at 11:00 am September 10",
      "Construction crew mobilized to remove damaged components",
      "Cleaning crew removed 50 barrels of solids and 80 barrels of oil",
      "Replaced fire tube, exhaust stack, and Stack Arrestor"
    ],
    "summary": "Heater treater burner malfunction caused excessive heat in exhaust stack, melting Stack Arrestor and collapsing exhaust stack. Temperature Safety High devices failed to activate. Operators continued operation for 12 hours despite stack glowing cherry red.",
